The paper deals with text-based image retrieval, which is a problem in computer vision. The use of scene graphs and graph matching also suggests a focus on computer vision techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of end-to-end training and neural networks suggests a focus on machine learning, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
